  <a href="#0" id="0">
   In this work, we proposed to treat punctuations as properties of context words for dependency parsing.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Experiments with an arc-standard parser showed that our method effectively improves parsing performance and we achieved the best accuracy for single-model transition-based parser.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Regarding punctuation processing for dependency parsing, Li et al.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   2010 ) proposed to utilize punctuations to segment sentences into small fragments and then parse the fragments separately.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   A similar approach is proposed by Spitkovsky et al.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   2011 ) which also designed a set of constraints on the fragments to improve unsupervised dependency parsing.
  </a>
